## Documentation Standards

### Markdown Formatting
- Use consistent header hierarchy
- Implement proper code block syntax highlighting
- Include table of contents for long documents
- Use relative links for internal references

### Code Examples
- Include relevant code snippets
- Use proper syntax highlighting
- Provide comments for complex logic
- Show both "bad" and "good" examples when applicable

### Diagram Standards
- Use ASCII diagrams for simple relationships
- Reference external diagram tools for complex architectures
- Include diagram keys and legends
- Ensure diagrams are accessible and clear

